001package io.cyborgcode.roa.framework.exceptions;
002
003/**
004 * Exception thrown when static test data cannot be initialized.
005 *
006 * <p>This runtime exception indicates a failure during the setup of static data
007 * required for tests, such as loading fixtures or pre-defined datasets.</p>
008 *
009 * @author Cyborg Code Syndicate üíçüë®üíª
010 */
011public class StaticTestDataInitializationException extends RuntimeException {
012
013   /**
014    * Constructs a new {@code StaticTestDataInitializationException} with the specified detail message
015    * and cause.
016    *
017    * @param message the detail message explaining the context of the initialization failure
018    * @param cause   the underlying exception that caused the failure
019    */
020   public StaticTestDataInitializationException(String message, Throwable cause) {
021      super(message, cause);
022   }
023
024   /**
025    * Constructs a new {@code StaticTestDataInitializationException} with a default message
026    * and the specified cause.
027    *
028    * @param cause the underlying exception that caused the failure
029    */
030   public StaticTestDataInitializationException(Throwable cause) {
031      super("Failed to initialize static test data", cause);
032   }
033}
